tsd:news_padi_web_2026_05_28_evropska_sredstva_za_okrevanje_in_odpornost_skupaj_do_cilja_trajnostna_kulturna_dediscina a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:2026-05-28-evropska-sredstva-za-okrevanje-in-odpornost-skupaj-do-cilja-trajnostna-kulturna-dediscina" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "fcc6449a30a4fc835d99a8301f3fb75865c6e9730f1216166ea2ec9392422051" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "European Recovery and Resilience Funds – Together towards the goal: sustainable cultural heritage" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# European Recovery and Resilience Funds – Together towards the goal: sustainable cultural heritage

European Recovery and Resilience Funds – Together towards the goal: sustainable cultural heritage

There are currently 31,095 heritage units registered in the Register of Immovable Cultural Heritage, of which 8,484 units have been declared a cultural monument of national or local importance.

The preserved cultural heritage significantly contributes to the visibility of the country and thus to the development of tourism, which was one of the most affected economic sectors during the COVID-19 pandemic.

The state and local communities are also striving to preserve the rich cultural heritage with the help of European funds.

As part of the Recovery and Resilience Plan (RRP), the Ministry of Culture, together with the municipalities, is implementing an investment for the sustainable restoration and revival of cultural heritage.

Sustainable restoration and revitalisation of cultural heritage and public cultural infrastructure – investment
The objective of the investment is to support the sustainable development of tourism through the revival of cultural heritage and public cultural infrastructure.

The investment shall include the renovation, renovation, integrated revitalisation and modernisation of public cultural heritage facilities.
€42 million from the Recovery and Resilience Facility (the Facility) is foreseen for the implementation of the investment.

To date, the state has already paid out more than EUR 31 million to project promoters for the project activities carried out.

Out of a total of 17 projects foreseen for funding, 14 projects have been fully completed, while the majority of the remaining projects must be completed by the end of June 2026.

All projects for the renovation of cultural monuments have been completed
owned by municipalities
:
Defenders of the Crown and Borders, project of restoration and revival of the ground floor of Črnomelj Castle and the city centre of Črnomelj,
Castle view experiences - Podčetrtek Castle,
The Castle on the Kozlov Edge – the past for the future,
Ormož Castle and Park in Architecture, Digital and Horticultural Transformation,
Podsreda Castle - cultural heritage and tourism,
Cultural experiences of the Jelšingrad Castle,
Cultural Incubator Štanjel,
Notranjski Museum Postojna - the third phase of the restoration of the garrison,
Radlje Mansion – the cultural and forest centre of the Upper Drava Valley,
Museum of Transport and Freighting,
Renovation of the buildings of the museum area of the Old Ironworks Ravne in Carinthia,
Pilon Gallery: A 5-star treasure trove of art.

Projects for the renovation of cultural monuments of national importance:
Comprehensive renovation of the Črnomelj Cultural Centre
– closed,
Vrba - Comprehensive renovation of the cultural monument
– closed,
Renovation of the house Vrba 1 next to the Prešeren homestead
– in implementation,
Comprehensive renovation of Negova Castle
– in implementation,
Comprehensive renovation of Turjak Castle
- in implementation.

All activities related to the investment objective must be completed by 31 August 2026 at the latest.

The milestone related to the selection of projects was implemented by Slovenia in the context of the third application for payment of European funds of the Mechanism, which was
EC fully disbursed in October 2024
.

The objective of the investment, which envisages the renovation of at least 15 cultural heritage sites, will be implemented by Slovenia with the last payment request, which will be sent to the EC by 30 September 2026 at the latest.""" ;
