tsd:news_padi_web_361979_koshka_umerla_posle_korma_s_ptichim_grippom_sud_zastavil_proizvoditelya_zaplatit_808_tysyach a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:361979-koshka-umerla-posle-korma-s-ptichim-grippom-sud-zastavil-proizvoditelya-zaplatit-808-tysyach" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "5077fd81765269b14ef5625b5af4324afe20905261516bea78c22bc00adaf9c6" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Cat died after food with bird flu: the court forced the manufacturer to pay $ 808 thousand" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Cat died after food with bird flu: the court forced the manufacturer to pay $ 808 thousand

Cat died after food with bird flu: the court forced the manufacturer to pay $ 808 thousand

23:12, 24 May 2026

A man won a court case after the death of a cat from dangerous food.

Photo: oregonlive.com

In the United States, a jury in Oregon awarded $808,000 to a Portland resident after his 4-year-old cat contracted bird flu and died after eating raw chicken pet food, writes Oregonlive.

The amount of compensation included 8 thousand dollars in veterinary costs, which Wild Coast Pet Foods must reimburse the owner of the cat, ----------.

During the two-day trial, Ganson's lawyers said the company assured customers that it would test raw food for bird flu, when it did not.

Ganson himself said that he trusted the manufacturer's statements when outbreaks of H5N1 on poultry farms began to spread rapidly in the United States in late 2024 and early 2025.

His Siamese cat, named Kira, fell ill a few days after eating Wild Coast Raw Free Range Chicken Formula food in late January 2025.

About a week later, the animal was already suffocating.

Veterinarians reported that there was no more chance to save the cat, after which the owner said goodbye to his pet.

"I just held her in my arms.

I told her how much I love her," ------ said.

Kira was euthanized on February 9, 2025.

The jury also ordered the company to pay $800,000 in punitive damages.

The cat's owner's lawyers argued that the producer acted with "deliberate indifference" to the health of the animals and their owners.

According to lawyer Michael ------, at least six cats died in Oregon after eating Wild Coast food, but ------ was the only owner to file a lawsuit.

During the trial, the lawyer released a video of the testimony of the founder of the company, ------------, who said that the food allegedly did not kill cats.

"I know that the feed made the animals sick.

But the owners themselves decided to euthanize the pet.

The feed itself did not kill the animal," Duncan said in recorded testimony.

The company's lawyers said Wild Coast did not act with malicious intent, but relied on a third-party laboratory to test products for H5N1 and other strains of bird flu.

Later, an expert in court said that the company's testing methods did not meet the "gold standard" as promised by the manufacturer.

According to the USDA, at least 135 domestic cats in 22 states have contracted bird flu since 2024.

Many of them became infected after eating raw chicken feed.

Subscribe to our Telegram channel t.me/sudua and Google News SUD.

UA, as well as on our VIBER and WhatsApp, Facebook and Instagram pages to keep abreast of the most important events.""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-24"^^xsd:date ;
