tsd:news_padi_web_amasyada_kanatli_hayvanlara_kus_gribi_taramasi a ts:NewsReport,
        ts:SourceDocument ;
    ts:referenceId "source_document:padi_web:amasyada-kanatli-hayvanlara-kus-gribi-taramasi" ;
    ts:sourceContentHash "78c24630f3bd41735f9f029659aedd2d95447d8ce9c125829581dd65928b923b" ;
    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "Bird Flu Screening for Poultry in Amasya" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# Bird Flu Screening for Poultry in Amasya

Bird Flu Screening for Poultry in Amasya

Amasya Provincial Directorate of Agriculture and Forestry carried out a comprehensive bird flu and newcastle control for poultry in Göynücek district.

Under the coordination of the Amasya Provincial Directorate of Agriculture and Forestry, an active survey study for poultry health was carried out by the ------------- of the Göynücek District Directorate of Agriculture and Forestry.

Within the scope of the studies carried out, field investigations and controls were carried out against Avian Influenza (Bird Flu) and Newcastle diseases that can be seen in poultry.

Necessary follow-up studies were carried out by ------------- for early diagnosis of diseases, prevention of their spread and protection of animal health.

Officials pointed out that regular screening and survey studies are of great importance in the fight against animal diseases and stated that producers should also comply with biosecurity rules sensitively.

Amasya Provincial Directorate of Agriculture and Forestry stated that field studies will continue uninterruptedly in order to protect animal health and prevent possible epidemics.""" ;
    ts:sourcePublishedDate "2026-05-25"^^xsd:date ;
