    ts:sourceDocumentTitle "--------- discusses urgent measures to combat lumpy skin disease in Milhan" ;
    ts:sourceFullText """# --------- discusses urgent measures to combat lumpy skin disease in Milhan

Al Mahwit discusses urgent measures to combat lumpy skin disease in Milhan

[Mon, 25 May 2026 20:40:12 +0300] 

 Mahwit - Saba:
The Agriculture Sector in Al Mahwit Governorate, along with the governorate branch of the Agricultural Cooperative Union, carried out emergency field interventions to confront the spread of lumpy skin disease affecting cattle in Milhan District.

The interventions aimed to reduce livestock deaths and protect animal wealth, which is considered one of the main sources of income for rural families.

During a meeting of the governorate’s Animal Health and Epidemiological Surveillance Department, attended by Deputy Agriculture Sector Officials ------------------- and ----------------------, participants discussed the epidemiological situation and rapid response mechanisms to contain the disease and limit its spread in affected areas.

The meeting approved the distribution of veterinary medicines provided by the Agriculture Sector and their handover to --------------, head of the Livestock Unit at the Milhan Veterinary Association, to treat infected cases and mitigate the impact of the disease on livestock.

Discussions also addressed the possibility of providing supplementary medicines, including fever reducers and vitamins, in coordination with private veterinary clinic owners.

The meeting further approved supplying agricultural associations with veterinary medicines and supplies through guarantees from the union branch and the governorate financing unit.

Head of the Agricultural Cooperative Union branch in the governorate, -------------------, affirmed that the interventions are part of an urgent plan to protect livestock and reduce mortality cases.

He expressed hope that the Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Water Resources would swiftly provide the necessary vaccines and strengthen preventive measures to curb the spread of the disease.

He also called on relevant authorities, the community, and livestock breeders to intensify biosecurity and veterinary guidance measures by isolating infected animals and ensuring proper care and nutrition.

Meanwhile, the union branch’s Secretary-General, -------------, stressed the importance of integrating official and community efforts to confront the disease, highlighting the role of media outlets in raising public awareness about prevention and control measures.""" ;
